wikipedia_page.main: Robert Beehoe Radcliffe (born 14 August 1797 in Westminster; died 26 August 1832 in Leamington, Warwickshire) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Cambridge University who was active in the 1810s. He is recorded in one match in 1819, totalling 6 runs with a highest score of 6 and taking 2 wickets.Radcliffe was educated at Eton and King's College, Cambridge. After graduating he became a Church of England priest and was vicar of Ashby-de-la-Zouch, Leicestershire, from 1828 until his death.
